 144:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****  * Using dynamic memory allocation requires to apply some changes to the linker file.
 145:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****  * ThreadX needs to pass a pointer to the first free memory location in RAM to the tx_application_d
 146:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****  * using the "first_unused_memory" argument.
 147:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****  * This require changes in the linker files to expose this memory location.
 148:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****  * For EWARM add the following section into the .icf file:
 149:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****      place in RAM_region    { last section FREE_MEM };
 150:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****  * For MDK-ARM
 151:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****      - either define the RW_IRAM1 region in the ".sct" file
 152:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****      - or modify the line below in "tx_initialize_low_level.S to match the memory region being used
 153:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****         LDR r1, =|Image$$RW_IRAM1$$ZI$$Limit|
 154:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c **** 
 155:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****  * For STM32CubeIDE add the following section into the .ld file:
 156:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****      ._threadx_heap :
 157:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****        {
 158:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****           . = ALIGN(8);
 159:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****           __RAM_segment_used_end__ = .;
 160:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****           . = . + 64K;
 161:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****           . = ALIGN(8);
 162:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****         } >RAM_D1 AT> RAM_D1
 163:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****     * The simplest way to provide memory for ThreadX is to define a new section, see ._threadx_heap
 164:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****     * In the example above the ThreadX heap size is set to 64KBytes.
 165:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****     * The ._threadx_heap must be located between the .bss and the ._user_heap_stack sections in the
 166:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****     * Caution: Make sure that ThreadX does not need more than the provided heap memory (64KBytes in
 167:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****     * Read more in STM32CubeIDE User Guide, chapter: "Linker script".
 168:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c **** 
 169:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****  * The "tx_initialize_low_level.S" should be also modified to enable the "USE_DYNAMIC_MEMORY_ALLOCA
 170:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c ****  */
 171:AZURE_RTOS/App/app_azure_rtos.c **** 
